<usermanual>
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

						The Stages of Change Readiness and Treatment Eagerness Scale (SOCRATES)
						(Version 8)
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

Script Author: Katja Borchert, Ph.D. (katjab@millisecond.com) for Millisecond Software, LLC
Date: 09-26-2023
last updated:  09-26-2023 by K. Borchert (katjab@millisecond.com) for Millisecond Software, LLC

Script Copyright © 09-26-2023 Millisecond Software

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
BACKGROUND INFO 	
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

This script implements Millisecond's computerized version of the 
The Stages of Change Readiness and Treatment Eagerness Scale (SOCRATES, Version 8).

Reference:

Miller, W. R., & Tonigan, J. S. (1996). Assessing drinkers’ motivation for change: The Stages of Change Readiness and 
Treatment Eagerness Scale (SOCRATES). Psychology of Addictive Behaviors 10, 81-89.
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
OVERVIEW
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

SOCRATES (version 8) is a self-report measure consisting of 19 5-point Likert Scale questions designed 
to assess readiness for change in alcohol abusers. 
The instrument provides three subscale scale scores: Recognition (Re), Ambivalence (Am), and Taking Steps (Ts). 
SOCRATES is a public domain instrument.

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
DURATION 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
the default set-up of the script takes appr. 3 minute to complete

__________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
DATA FILE INFORMATION 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
The default data stored in the data files are:

(1) Raw data file: 'socrates_v8.iqdat'

date, time:						date and time script was run with the current group/subjectnumber 
subject, group, session:	  	with the current subject/groupnumber/session id
build:							the Inquisit build 

q*_response:					response given (in assigned values)
								Scale: 1 (almost never) - 4 (almost always)
								R: reversed coded questions (if any)
									
q*_latency:						how much time (in ms) the participant spent on the surveypage with this particular 
								question (the last time this particular surveypage was visited)

(2) Summary data file: 'socrates_v8_summary*.iqdat'

inquisit.version:				Inquisit version run
computer.platform:				the platform the script was run on (win/mac/ios/android)
startDate:						date script was run
startTime:						time script was started
subjectid:						assigned subject id number
groupid:						assigned group id number
sessionid:						assigned session id number
elapsedTime:					time it took to run script (in ms); measured from onset to offset of script
completed:						0 = script was not completed (prematurely aborted); 
								1 = script was completed (all conditions run)	
							
socrates_RE:					Recognition subscale: q1_Re,q3_Re,q7_Re,q10_Re,q12_Re,q15_Re,q17_Re (Range:7-35)
								The higher the score, the higher Recognition that there is a problem with alcohol
								
socrates_AM:					Ambivalence subscale:q2_Am,q6_Am,q11_Am,q16_Am (Range: 4-20)
								The higher the score, the higher Ambivalence/Uncertainty towards drinking.
								High scores show some openess to recognition
								(Note: should be interpreted in light of recognition score)
								
socrates_TS:					Taking Steps subscale: q4_Ts,q5_Ts,q8_Ts,q9_Ts,q13_Ts,q14_Ts,q18_Ts,q19_Ts (Range: 8-40)
								The higher the score, the more steps participant reports to have taken to 
								to deal with drinking problems.
								
															
socrates_total:					sum of all subscores (Range: 19-95)							

</usermanual>

**************************************************************************************************************
				!!!REMAINING CODE: Customize after careful consideration only!!!
**************************************************************************************************************

**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	DEFAULTS
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
script requires Inquisit 6.6.1.0 or higher

<defaults>
/ canvasaspectratio = (4,3)
/ minimumversion = "6.6.1.0"
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ txbgcolor = white
/ txcolor = (0, 0, 0)
</defaults>


**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	DATA
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************

Note: data file explanations under User Manual Information at the top

***********************
raw data file
***********************

***********************
summary data file
***********************
<summarydata>
/ columns = (inquisit.version, computer.platform, script.startDate, script.startTime, 
script.subjectId, script.groupId, script.sessionId, 
script.elapsedTime, script.completed,
expressions.socrates_RE, expressions.socrates_AM, expressions.socrates_TS, expressions.socrates_total

//raw responses:
radiobuttons.q1_Re.response,
radiobuttons.q2_Am.response,
radiobuttons.q3_Re.response,
radiobuttons.q4_Ts.response,
radiobuttons.q5_Ts.response,
radiobuttons.q6_Am.response,
radiobuttons.q7_Re.response,
radiobuttons.q8_Ts.response,
radiobuttons.q9_Ts.response,
radiobuttons.q10_Re.response,
radiobuttons.q11_Am.response,
radiobuttons.q12_Re.response,
radiobuttons.q13_Ts.response,
radiobuttons.q14_Ts.response,
radiobuttons.q15_Re.response,
radiobuttons.q16_Am.response,
radiobuttons.q17_Re.response,
radiobuttons.q18_Ts.response,
radiobuttons.q19_Ts.response)
</summarydata>

**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	EXPRESSIONS
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************

<expressions>
/ socrates_RE = return (radiobuttons.q1_Re.response + radiobuttons.q3_Re.response + radiobuttons.q7_Re.response +
radiobuttons.q10_Re.response + radiobuttons.q12_Re.response + radiobuttons.q15_Re.response + radiobuttons.q17_Re.response)

/ socrates_AM = return (radiobuttons.q2_Am.response + radiobuttons.q6_Am.response + radiobuttons.q11_Am.response + 
radiobuttons.q16_Am.response)

/ socrates_TS = return (radiobuttons.q4_Ts.response + radiobuttons.q5_Ts.response + radiobuttons.q8_Ts.response + 
radiobuttons.q9_Ts.response + radiobuttons.q13_Ts.response + radiobuttons.q14_Ts.response + radiobuttons.q18_Ts.response +
radiobuttons.q19_Ts.response)

/ socrates_total = return (expressions.socrates_RE + expressions.socrates_AM + expressions.socrates_TS)
</expressions>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	QUESTIONS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
Note: by default all questions are required to be answered. To change
/required = false

<radiobuttons q1_Re>
/ caption = "1. I really want to make changes in my drinking."
/ options = ("<b>NO!</b><br>Strongly<br>Disagree", "<b>No</b><br><br>Disagree", 
"<b>?</b><br>Undecided or<br>Unsure", "<b>Yes</b><br><br>Agree", "<b>YES!</b><br>Strongly<br>Agree")
/ optionValues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5")
/ required = true
/ orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q2_Am>
/ caption = "2. Sometimes I wonder if I am an alcoholic."
/ options = ("<b>NO!</b><br>Strongly<br>Disagree", "<b>No</b><br><br>Disagree", 
"<b>?</b><br>Undecided or<br>Unsure", "<b>Yes</b><br><br>Agree", "<b>YES!</b><br>Strongly<br>Agree")
/ optionValues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5")
/ required = true
/ orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q3_Re>
/ caption = "3. If I don’t change my drinking soon, my problems are going to get worse."
/ options = ("<b>NO!</b><br>Strongly<br>Disagree", "<b>No</b><br><br>Disagree", 
"<b>?</b><br>Undecided or<br>Unsure", "<b>Yes</b><br><br>Agree", "<b>YES!</b><br>Strongly<br>Agree")
/ optionValues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5")
/ required = true
/ orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q4_Ts>
/ caption = "4. I have already started making some changes in my drinking."
/ options = ("<b>NO!</b><br>Strongly<br>Disagree", "<b>No</b><br><br>Disagree", 
"<b>?</b><br>Undecided or<br>Unsure", "<b>Yes</b><br><br>Agree", "<b>YES!</b><br>Strongly<br>Agree")
/ optionValues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5")
/ required = true
/ orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q5_Ts>
/ caption = "5. I was drinking too much at one time, but I’ve managed to change my drinking."
/ options = ("<b>NO!</b><br>Strongly<br>Disagree", "<b>No</b><br><br>Disagree", 
"<b>?</b><br>Undecided or<br>Unsure", "<b>Yes</b><br><br>Agree", "<b>YES!</b><br>Strongly<br>Agree")
/ optionValues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5")
/ required = true
/ orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q6_Am>
/ caption = "6. Sometimes I wonder if my drinking is hurting other people."
/ options = ("<b>NO!</b><br>Strongly<br>Disagree", "<b>No</b><br><br>Disagree", 
"<b>?</b><br>Undecided or<br>Unsure", "<b>Yes</b><br><br>Agree", "<b>YES!</b><br>Strongly<br>Agree")
/ optionValues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5")
/ required = true
/ orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q7_Re>
/ caption = "7. I am a problem drinker."
/ options = ("<b>NO!</b><br>Strongly<br>Disagree", "<b>No</b><br><br>Disagree", 
"<b>?</b><br>Undecided or<br>Unsure", "<b>Yes</b><br><br>Agree", "<b>YES!</b><br>Strongly<br>Agree")
/ optionValues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5")
/ required = true
/ orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q8_Ts>
/ caption = "8. I’m not just thinking about changing my drinking, I’m already doing something about it."
/ options = ("<b>NO!</b><br>Strongly<br>Disagree", "<b>No</b><br><br>Disagree", 
"<b>?</b><br>Undecided or<br>Unsure", "<b>Yes</b><br><br>Agree", "<b>YES!</b><br>Strongly<br>Agree")
/ optionValues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5")
/ required = true
/ orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q9_Ts>
/ caption = "9. I have already changed my drinking, and I am looking for ways to keep from slipping back to my old pattern."
/ options = ("<b>NO!</b><br>Strongly<br>Disagree", "<b>No</b><br><br>Disagree", 
"<b>?</b><br>Undecided or<br>Unsure", "<b>Yes</b><br><br>Agree", "<b>YES!</b><br>Strongly<br>Agree")
/ optionValues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5")
/ required = true
/ orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q10_Re>
/ caption = "10. I have serious problems with drinking."
/ options = ("<b>NO!</b><br>Strongly<br>Disagree", "<b>No</b><br><br>Disagree", 
"<b>?</b><br>Undecided or<br>Unsure", "<b>Yes</b><br><br>Agree", "<b>YES!</b><br>Strongly<br>Agree")
/ optionValues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5")
/ required = true
/ orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q11_Am>
